<sect1 id="inserting">
<title>Inserting Events</title>

<para>&konsolekalendar; can insert events into a &kde; calendar using the
<parameter>--add</parameter> command line argument.</para>

<para>In the following example, an event starting on 2003-06-04 (June 4, 2003)
at 1000 and ending at 1200 with summary "Doctor Visit" will be
inserted into the user's default calendar:</para>

<informalexample>
<para>
<prompt>%</prompt><userinput>
<command>konsolekalendar</command>
<option>--add</option>
<option>--date <replaceable>2003-06-04</replaceable></option>
<option>--time <replaceable>10:00</replaceable></option>
<option>--end-time <replaceable>12:00</replaceable></option>
<option>--summary <replaceable>"Doctor Visit"</replaceable></option>
</userinput>
</para>
</informalexample>

<para>In this example, a birthday event is added into the user's default calendar:</para>

<informalexample>
<para>
<prompt>%</prompt><userinput>
<command>konsolekalendar</command>
<option>--add</option>
<option>--date <replaceable>2003-06-06</replaceable></option>
<option>--summary <replaceable>"My Birthday"</replaceable></option>
<option>--description <replaceable>"Party Time"</replaceable></option>
</userinput>
</para>
</informalexample>

<tip><para>
TODO:  To add a birthday, holiday, anniversary, etc. into
the calendar as a <emphasis>free</emphasis> event (that is,
an event that does not take up space in the day) use the
additional command line option <option>--time=free</option>.
</para>
</tip>

<para>Here a week vacation is inserted into our default calendar:</para>

<informalexample>
<para>
<prompt>%</prompt><userinput>
<command>konsolekalendar</command>
<option>--add</option>
<option>--date <replaceable>2003-08-01</replaceable></option>
<option>--end-date <replaceable>2003-08-20</replaceable></option>
<option>--summary <replaceable>"Vacation"</replaceable></option>
<option>--description <replaceable>"Nobody will ever find me!"</replaceable></option>
</userinput>
</para>
</informalexample>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="deleting">
<title>Removing Entries</title>

<para>&konsolekalendar; can remove events from a &kde; calendar using the
<parameter>--delete</parameter> command line argument.</para>

<warning>
<para>
The delete feature has not been thoroughly tested yet.
USE AT YOUR OWN RISK!
</para>
</warning>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="changing">
<title>Modifying Entries</title>

<para>&konsolekalendar; can modify existing events into a &kde; calendar
using the <parameter>--change</parameter> command line argument.</para>

<warning>
<para>
The change feature has not been thoroughly tested yet.
USE AT YOUR OWN RISK!
</para>
</warning>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="exporting">
<title>Exporting to Other Formats</title>

<para>&konsolekalendar; can export a &kde; calendar to other well known
formats using the <parameter>--export-type</parameter> command line argument.</para>

</sect1>

</chapter>

<chapter id="features-commandline-options">
